Persistent Memory Development Kit

This is src/test/tools/grandetecto/README.

Long-time ago in the Wild West, cowboys solved their problems using revolvers.
So far, pmemdetect efficiently defended PMDK users from persistent robbers,
but new enemies: ADR and eADR beat him. Now, we have grandetecto. This 'grande'
tool detects supported granularity by given 'path' argument. For example, if we
want to check availability to requested staore granularity equal cache line we
should use grandetecto as follow: grandetecto -p /mnt/pmem.

It's used as a 'smoked test' before running RUNTESTS.

Usage:
	$ grandetecto <-b|-c|-p|-h> <path>

Available options:
 -b     -- check if given path has byte granularity
 -c     -- check if given path has cache line granularity
 -p     -- check if given path has page granularity
 -h     -- print usage info

